f how to restore and maintain flood defences in target condition.” He said a long-term strategy for flood protection running to 2021 would be delivered by the autumn.</p><p>Pickles criticised the Environment Agency chairman, Lord Smith, who had suggested there was a choice between protecting “front rooms or farmland”, with Pickles saying lessons would be learned from recent problems including “the local accountability of quangos”.</p><p>Shadow environment secretary, Maria Eagle, said: “The government was caught out by the floods and it took far too long for ministers to realised the seriousness of the situation. There have been 21 meeting of [emergency committee] Cobra but it is far from clear what all the talk has achieved.” She also accused ministers of “fiddling the figures” over flood defence spending, after Pickles used a different baseline from that of Cameron on Wednesday. Annual flood defence spending fell by 15% under the coalition.</p><p>Pickles, who was standing in for the environment secretary, Owen Paterson, who is having emergency eye surgery, also confirmed changes to the Bellwin scheme, through which councils can claim funding for damage repairs. They will be able to claim 100% of losses over a threshold, not 85%, and will have to the end of March to claim.  </p><p>On the severing of the mainline London-Penzance railway after a sea wall collapsed at Dawlish, Pickles said: “We are not in a position to know how long it will take [to repair].”</p></blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f38567e4b0d5e31a93fefe\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:59:03.559Z\">12.59pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Steven Morris has been talking to more victims of the floods on the Somerset Levels, including John Field from Moorland. <br></p><p>He said a decision by Somerset police to use a megaphone from a helicopter to urge people to flee their homes created \"pandemonium.\" Field said \"it just frightened people.\" <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G6BHgRhmvaA\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/G6BHgRhmvaA?wmode=opaque&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure> <p>Steven also uploaded this brief clip of the water scene in the village. <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-video\" data-canonical-url=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-2VO1rVs20M\"                                                                                > <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"259\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-2VO1rVs20M?wmode=opaque&feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f3827ce4b0d5e31a93fefa\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:39:26.479Z\">12.39pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-fe9cb17d-c3be-44d6-a256-7e17cac40dbd\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/6/1391690358617/a16d4ff6-31f6-41dc-91dc-f003e511625d-460x276.jpeg\" alt=\"A giant wave totally engulfes a coastal pub at Chesil Beach in Dorset\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>A giant wave totally engulfes a coastal pub at Chesil Beach in Dorset. Photograph: Paul McEvily/knsnews.co.uk</figcaption> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:46:55.360Z\">at 12.46pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37a3fe4b0d5e31a93fef0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:10:46.382Z\">12.10pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Here's the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/speeches/government-action-taken-to-respond-to-floods-and-extreme-weather\">full text of the statement by Eric Pickles</a>.</p><p>These are some of the key segments: <br></p><blockquote class=\"quoted\">This January has been the wettest since George III was on the throne..We will continue to face severe weather well into next week. I want to put on the record my utmost sympathy for those affected.<p>Flooding has devastating effects on communities. <br></p>I can announce that the government will provide an additional £130 million for emergency repairs and maintenance: £30 million in the current year and £100 million next year. This will cover costs incurred during the current emergency response and recovery, as well as essential repairs to ensure that defences are maintained.<br><br><p>The full picture of the damage caused to flood defences has not yet emerged and the weather continues to be savage. The government will therefore carry out a rapid review of the additional work needed to restore our flood defences and maintain them in target condition.</p><p>In addition, I am publishing before the House today details of how my department is enhancing the terms of the Bellwin scheme ...<br></p><p>The additional funding that we have outlined today will allow the government’s programme of capital investment to continue, fulfilling our commitment to improving defences throughout England.</p><p>We have already put in place investment plans to improve the protection to at least 465,000 households by the end of the decade.</p><p>But, in addition, we are today announcing 42 new flood defence schemes for 2014 to 2015.</p><p>Together with other projects beginning construction in 2014-15, this will protect more than 42,000 households.</p><p>This includes schemes in:</p><ul><li>Salford which will improve protection for more than 2,000 homes and businesses</li><li>Clacton where more than 3,000 homes are currently at risk</li><li>Willerby in the East Riding of Yorkshire where more than 8,000 properties will be better protected</li></ul><p>There are also smaller, but no less important, schemes in Lincoln, Stockton and Todmorden.</p><p>We will work to defend both town and country. For the record, I do not agree with the comments of Lord Smith who implied there is a choice between the two.</p><p>Looking further forward, we have made an unprecedented long-term 6-year commitment to record levels of capital investment in improving defences:</p><ul><li>£370 million in 2015 to 2016</li><li>and then the same in real terms each year</li><li>rising to over £400 million by the end of this decade</li></ul>After the dark skies clear, there will be lessons to learn:<ul><li>from the way we help local authorities</li><li>to the role of quangos and the need for local accountability</li><li>to the influence of man-made policies on dredging and tree planting on our landscape and rivers</li><li>to the resilience of our nation as a whole in the 21st century</li></ul><p>The measures that the Coalition Government has announced today provides an clear commitment to reduce the risks of flooding and coastal erosion.</p><p>The additional funding means that, over this Parliament, this government will be investing more than £3.1 billion, compared to £2.7 billion in the previous 5 years under the last government.</p><p>This is more than ever before, and we will spend it well and spend it wisely.</p><p>We cannot control the weather. But we can and will provide the security that hard-working people deserve to allow them to get on with their daily lives.</p></blockquote> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:14:23.382Z\">at 12.14pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f378f0e4b0d5e31a93feec\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:00:20.125Z\">12.00pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Pickles said it was \"utterly ridiculous\" to expect an update on when the damaged railway at Dawlish would be repaired. He said Network Rail were busy trying to protect the line from the next storm and high tides. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37864e4b0019d0eaa7f20\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:57:58.570Z\">11.57am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Eagle urged Pickles to end the Environment Agency's premium rate phone line on flood advice. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f377c2e4b0019d0eaa7f1f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:55:07.514Z\">11.55am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Shadow environment secretary Maria Eagle responded to the Pickles statement by claiming the government is fiddling the figures on cuts to flood defences and the extra funding on repairs. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f376d8e4b0d5e31a93feea\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:52:33.254Z\">11.52am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Guardian columnist George Monbiot, who has warned against dredging, gives a mixed reaction to Pickles' statement. <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/GeorgeMonbiot/statuses/431393900364713984\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Eric Pickles is living in a dream world: a world in which neither fields nor towns need be flooded. Magical thinking. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23flooding&amp;src=hash\">#flooding</a></p>&mdash; GeorgeMonbiot (@GeorgeMonbiot) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GeorgeMonbiot/statuses/431393900364713984\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/GeorgeMonbiot/statuses/431394442096832512\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>But at least Pickles has now mentioned tree planting as a means of mitigating <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23flooding&amp;src=hash\">#flooding</a> - slowly the message is getting through.</p>&mdash; GeorgeMonbiot (@GeorgeMonbiot) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GeorgeMonbiot/statuses/431394442096832512\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37699e4b0d5e31a93fee9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:49:35.222Z\">11.49am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Pickles conceded \"there are lessons to be learned\" from the flooding crisis, including on dredging and planting in uplands. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37630e4b0019d0eaa7f1d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:48:28.308Z\">11.48am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>\"We will work to defend both town and country\" Pickles says in reference to comments made by Lord Smith the chairman of the Environment Agency.  Pickles says Smith was wrong to imply that Britain did not have enough resources to protect both. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37602e4b0d5e31a93fee8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:46:45.536Z\">11.46am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Pickles announced 42 new flood defence schemes to protect 42,000 homes. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37580e4b0d5e31a93fee7\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:45:58.415Z\">11.45am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Pickles also set out changes to the Bellwin formula for funding councils faced with emergencies. </p><p>There's <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/more-support-for-communities-affected-by-floods\">more on the changes here</a>. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f3753de4b0019d0eaa7f1a\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:43:51.057Z\">11.43am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The government is to make an extra £130m available in the next two years for repairing flood defences, Pickles announced. <br></p><p>He also promised a \"rapid review\" of flood defences. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f374bfe4b0d5e31a93fee4\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:42:21.045Z\">11.42am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Pickles says \"we have all be struck\" by images of flood stricken communities on the Somerset Levels. He paid tribute to the Environment Agency workers and the emergency services who have been through \"hell and high water\".</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37464e4b0019d0eaa7f17\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:40:38.167Z\">11.40am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Eric Pickles begins his statement by passing his best wishes on to Environment Secretary Owen Paterson who is in hospital for a detached retina. <br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f3732ae4b0d5e31a93fee2\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:36:27.325Z\">11.36am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Meanwhile, on the Somerset Levels the water is still rising according to Steven Morris. <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431390810656219136\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Les and Sue Chapman in the village of Moorland. Mr C: The water is still rising. <a href=\"http://t.co/4z28npNk5n\">pic.twitter.com/4z28npNk5n</a></p>&mdash; steven morris  (@stevenmorris20) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431390810656219136\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431389828979380224\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Moorland on the Somerset Levels <a href=\"http://t.co/ENae9Xu3y5\">pic.twitter.com/ENae9Xu3y5</a></p>&mdash; steven morris  (@stevenmorris20) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431389828979380224\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431390325018738688\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Graveyard at the village of Moorland on the Somerset Levels <a href=\"http://t.co/Xxcd781BIu\">pic.twitter.com/Xxcd781BIu</a></p>&mdash; steven morris  (@stevenmorris20) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431390325018738688\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431390440777322496\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Sodden carpets in Moorland, Somerset Levels. <a href=\"http://t.co/X9qCJe23Hc\">pic.twitter.com/X9qCJe23Hc</a></p>&mdash; steven morris  (@stevenmorris20) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/stevenmorris20/statuses/431390440777322496\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:37:56.981Z\">at 11.37am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f372bce4b0d5e31a93fee1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:33:41.959Z\">11.33am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>While we still wait for the Commons statement by Eric Pickles, the BBC's Norman Smith says this afternoon's Cobra committee meeting has been delayed until this evening, and will be chaired by the PM.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/BBCNormanS/statuses/431389517304848384\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>PM to chair another floods  COBRA meeting this evening instead of one this afternoon that was to have been chaired by Eric Pickles</p>&mdash; norman smith (@BBCNormanS) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/BBCNormanS/statuses/431389517304848384\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37224e4b0019d0eaa7f15\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:31:04.549Z\">11.31am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Labour press officer Callum Collins reckons that without the Beeching cuts to the railway network, yesterday's damage to the line at Dawlish would not have been so disruptive. <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/callumcollins/statuses/431388820974473216\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Map of Devon <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23railways&amp;src=hash\">#railways</a> in 30s shows how, without Beeching, the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Dawlish&amp;src=hash\">#Dawlish</a> collapse wouldn&#39;t be quite so catastrophic. <a href=\"http://t.co/0WVnjdMDjn\">pic.twitter.com/0WVnjdMDjn</a></p>&mdash; Callum Collins (@callumcollins) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/callumcollins/statuses/431388820974473216\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f36e82e4b0019d0eaa7f10\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:15:18.204Z\">11.15am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Here are the areas currently covered by the amber<a href=\"https://twitter.com/metoffice/status/431026923636916224\"> \"be prepared\" warnings from the Met Office</a>. <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/metoffice/statuses/431026923636916224\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Amber &#39;be prepared&#39; warnings have been issued for rain and wind <a href=\"http://t.co/PQe7z2ueZK\">http://t.co/PQe7z2ueZK</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23ukstorm&amp;src=hash\">#ukstorm</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/rguMr8ByY5\">pic.twitter.com/rguMr8ByY5</a></p>&mdash; Met Office (@metoffice) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/metoffice/statuses/431026923636916224\">February 5, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> <p>The Environment Agency still has two severe flood warnings in place for Somerset. But it has <a href=\"http://www.environment-agency.gov.uk/homeandleisure/floods/31618.aspx\">reduced the number of flood warnings across the rest of the country to 57</a> with a 217 flood alerts in place. <br></p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:19:13.869Z\">at 11.19am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f36c46e4b0019d0eaa7f0d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:07:01.897Z\">11.07am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>David Cameron has defended Owen Paterson's handling of the flooding crisis, insisting he was \"absolutely on top\" of the issue, PA reports. </p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>In an interview on BBC Manchester, the prime minister insisted that the government had been \"very proactive\" in putting its emergency planning procedures into action as soon as the stormy weather hit. </p><p>When presenter Mike Sweeney questioned Environment Secretary's Paterson's decision to view flooding in Somerset \"dressed for a ball at the Ritz, without his wellies\", Cameron responded: \"I completely disagree with what you said about Owen Paterson, who knows a lot about rural issues and the countryside. He sits for a rural seat. He is absolutely on top of those flooding issues. </p><p>\"He went to visit the floods. He was not dressed as if he was going to the Ritz, he was dressed as if he was going to floods. He had a pair of wellies, but because he was harassed as soon as he got out of his car, he didn't have a chance to put them on. He didn't forget. </p><p>\"Honestly, some of these things that get going on the media have to be challenged, because otherwise a lie is halfway around the world before the truth can get its boots on, and that's a rather appropriate expression in these circumstances.\" </p><p>The PM was critical of the Environment Agency's decision to cut back on dredging rivers over the past two decades. </p><p>\"The fact is, since the Environment Agency was founded in the late 1990s, it took a view - and increasingly other organisations took a view - that dredging wasn't appropriate,\" he said. \"I think that's wrong. I have a constituency that does flood frequently. I pushed for dredging and some dredging has taken place and it does make a difference. </p><p>\"We've got to make sure that our system is focused on protecting people above all else, so some of the arguments against dredging have to be taken on and we need to start dredging again more systematically. The Environment Agency now accepts that.\" </p><p>He added: \"The scale of these weather events and the scale of the flooding has shifted even more something that was beginning to shift anyway. The Environment Agency had taken a very anti-dredging view for many years. That was beginning to change and now it's changing faster, and that's something I welcome.\" </p></blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f36b44e4b0019d0eaa7f0b\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:03:45.319Z\">11.03am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Guardian readers continue to share their pictures of the impact of the floods via <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0dd85e4b08e6aaede60d3\">GuardianWitness</a>. Here's a  couple of selections from some of the latest submissions. <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-witness element-witness-image\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\" data-media-id=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0dd85e4b08e6aaede60d3/801584\"> <div class=\"element-witness--main\"> <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0dd85e4b08e6aaede60d3/801584\" itemprop=\"url\"><img src=\"https://n0tice-static.s3.amazonaws.com/image/1391625121508517daa6c2d2b2838adf9dd6f838c28c2-mediumoriginalaspectdouble.jpg\" alt=\"Flooded road near Dawlish\" itemprop=\"contentURL\"/></a> <figcaption> <h3 class=\"element-witness--title\" itemprop=\"name\"><a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0dd85e4b08e6aaede60d3/801584\" itemprop=\"url\">Flooded road near Dawlish</a></h3> <div itemprop=\"description\"> <p>Flooded road just up the road from where today&#39;s storm destroyed part of the train line near Dawlish, Devon.</p> </div> </figcaption> </div> <footer class=\"element-witness--footer\"> <p class=\"element-witness--source\">Sent via <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/\" class=\"element-witness--brand\" itemprop=\"provider\">GuardianWitness</a></p> <div class=\"element-witness--metadata\"> <p class=\"element-witness--author\" itemprop=\"author\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\"> By <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/user/Fleurdenel\" class=\"element-witness--author-name\" itemprop=\"name\">Fleurdenel</a> </p> <p class=\"element-witness--date\"> <time itemprop=\"dateCreated\" datetime=\"2014-02-05T18:32:01Z\">5 February 2014, 18:32</time> </p> </div> </footer> </figure> <figure class=\"element element-witness element-witness-image\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\" data-media-id=\"http