>1.09pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Summary</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <ul><li><b>That's it from the live blog but <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/06/london-tube-strike-second-day-underground-tfl-overground\">here's an analysis of the strikes so far</a></b> from our transport correspondent, Gwyn Topham.</li></ul><ul><li><b>The latest from <a href=\"http://www.tfl.gov.uk/tfl/livetravelnews/realtime/tube/default.html\">TfL live updates</a> shows that the Overgound is now operating a good service after earlier delays. </b> The Bakerloo and Northern lines have reopened from Charing Cross station, and the Northern line and DLR remain unaffected by strike action.</li></ul><ul><li><b>All other underground lines are operating limited services, except Central and Waterloo &amp; City lines, which are closed. </b>Open lines are vulnerable to closure or further restrictions until the walk-out ends at 9pm Thursday night so keep this in mind for your homeward journey</li></ul><ul><li><b>Road congestion has largely cleared in and around central London.</b> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TfLTrafficNews\">TfL Traffic News</a>, however, reports delays currently at the Blackwall Tunnel<br></li></ul><ul><li><b>Bus services are also returning to normal.</b> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TfLBusAlerts\">TfL Bus Alerts</a> still reminds travelers that: <br><p>\"Buses are busier than usual, please allow more time for your journey.\"</p></li><li><b>Need a chuckle after your commute?</b> Try this collection of <a href=\"http://www.buzzfeed.com/scottybryan/the-best-of-the-internets-reaction-to-the-tube-strike\">the internet's best reactions</a> to the walk-out courtesy of Buzzfeed.<br></li></ul> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f38154e4b0019d0eaa7f2b\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:38:12.909Z\">12.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>There is a long queue for taxis outside Paddington station. <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/bbclondon\">BBC London Radio</a> have spoken to one black cab driver, Steven Murray, who advises people to walk instead:</p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>A £10 journey can turn into £20-25. I've been telling people it's a 45 minute walk but that's your best option.</p></blockquote> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/AstleyMedia/statuses/431398644794019840\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Don&#39;t think we&#39;ll join the taxi queue! <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/4hwzuJoMi0\">pic.twitter.com/4hwzuJoMi0</a></p>&mdash; Astley Media (@AstleyMedia) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/AstleyMedia/statuses/431398644794019840\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37e9ee4b0019d0eaa7f27\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:23:55.416Z\">12.23pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>If cycling doesn't appeal, others have been using social media to link up with fellow walkers for a more sociable journey home.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/f_sd/statuses/431394193924050944\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Anybody fancy walking from Waterloo to Hackney tonight? <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a></p>&mdash; Fernando Sdrigotti (@f_sd) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/f_sd/statuses/431394193924050944\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37579e4b0019d0eaa7f1c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T12:05:25.482Z\">12.05pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Twitter has been active with cyclists using the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?src=typd&amp;q=%23BikeTheStrike\">#BiketheStrike</a> hashtag - a fairly even mix of regular riders and those on their bikes or using cycle hire strictly out of necessity. Boris Johnson <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MayorofLondon/status/431039532998217728\">tweeted</a> that TfL are reporting a 70% increase in cycle hire use during strike days.<br></p><p>The spirit of solidarity has led one blogging biker to think up a way of encourging more people to commute on two wheels. <a href=\"http://ibikelondon.blogspot.co.uk/\">ibikelondon</a>'s <a href=\"https://mapsengine.google.com/map/u/1/edit?mid=zvf49i9nysNA.kqfdt3zLBRmo&amp;authuser=1\">editable map</a> allows any Londoner to share their routes to work in the hope that they will team up with others who don't usually cycle.</p><p>Even with today's strike ending at 9pm, this could come in handy next Tuesday if a second strike is not called off after dispute negotiations tomorrow.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-embed\" data-canonical-url=\"\"data-alt=\"Regular cyclists share their routes to work so that less confident riders can join them during the tube strike\"> <iframe src=\"https://mapsengine.google.com/map/u/0/embed?mid=zvf49i9nysNA.kqfdt3zLBRmo\" width=\"460\" height=\"345\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe> <figcaption>Regular cyclists share their routes so that less confident riders can join them during the tube strike</figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f37156e4b0019d0eaa7f14\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:33:38.746Z\">11.33am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Transport expert Dr John Disney, a senior lecturer at  <a href=\"http://www.ntu.ac.uk/nbs/index.html\">Nottingham Business School</a>, who was previously a consultant to the Department for Transport, has said that the decision to close all London Underground ticket offices should be reconsidered for the sake of visitors from around the UK and overseas:<br></p><blockquote class=\"quoted\">Every city and area in the UK has its own public transport ticketing systems ... confused passengers would rather queue at a ticket office window than do battle with a ticket machine with agitated commuters breathing down their necks.</blockquote><blockquote><p>The Tube can be a baffling, and indeed frightening, experience for unfamiliar travellers and the ticket office is often regarded as a sanctuary.</p></blockquote><p>Rather than remove over 900 front-line staff, Dr Disney urges a compromise, which both parties at tomorrow's dispute mediation talks could consider: <br></p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>Retain the busiest central London ticket offices and to ensure that gate staff at all outer London stations are fully trained to assist passengers to use the ticket machines.</p></blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f36532e4b0d5e31a93fecf\" class=\"block is-summary\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T10:51:57.404Z\">10.51am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Summary</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <ul><li><b>Underground and mainline trains:</b> despite congestion at stations caused by crowd control measures by TfL staff and police, commuters on trains have generally reported smoother travel and quieter trains this morning compared to yesterday. <br></li></ul><ul><li><b>The Overground is <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/06/london-tube-strike-day-two-live?commentpage=1#block-52f34e12e4b0ab978b0f9778\">subject severe and minor delays</a> at various points</b>, mostly due to crowd calming but also caused by a signal fault and an early freight train breakdown. <br></li></ul><ul><li><b>Travelers above ground <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/06/london-tube-strike-day-two-live?commentpage=1#block-52f36209e4b0d5e31a93fecc\">face queues at stops and significant delays to journeys</a> by bus.</b> Congestion on the roads as also been compounded by more people opting to travel in by car.</li></ul><ul><li><b>Underground lines: the Waterloo &amp; City and Circle lines remain closed due to the strike.</b> All other underground lines are operating limited services except the Northern line, which is operating in full. The DLR is also unaffected. Full details from <a href=\"http://www.tfl.gov.uk/tfl/livetravelnews/realtime/tube/default.html\">TfL live updates</a>.</li></ul><ul><li><b>The <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/06/tube-strike-misery-commuters-talks-friday\">Press Associated reported</a> that Acas will mediate talks on Friday.</b> The talks between London Underground and the transport unions, TSSA and RMT, are aimed at averting further tube strike action on Tuesday and Wednesday of next week.<br></li></ul><ul><li><b>Boris Johnson and Bob Crow appeared separately on <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01q9zc7\">BBC Radio London</a> just after 9am</b>. The mayor also appeared to give press interviews <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/06/london-tube-strike-day-two-live?commentpage=1#block-52f35602e4b0530e249db07chttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/06/london-tube-strike-day-two-live?commentpage=1#block-52f35602e4b0530e249db07c\">outside Embankment station</a>.<br></li></ul> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T11:22:12.607Z\">at 11.22am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f36209e4b0d5e31a93fecc\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T10:34:09.860Z\">10.34am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>TfL are reporting moderate crowds yet delays of 40 minutes for buses from key locations such as King's Cross, Euston, Waterloo, London Bridge, Victoria, Brixton and Stratford. Elsewhere, the 55 route via Oxford Street is currently running with journey times of up to two hours.</p><p>The Metropolitan line bus replacement service between Uxbridge and Harrow-on-the-Hill has now been stopped. However, the underground line continues to run into central London between Harrow-on-the-Hill and Aldgate.<br></p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f360d3e4b0d5e31a93fec8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T10:19:53.195Z\">10.19am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Londonist has an <a href=\"http://londonist.com/2014/02/a-look-at-the-reasons-behind-the-tube-strike.php\">in-depth look</a> at the reasons behind the tube strikes:</p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>TfL thinks it will need an extra 200 staff to run the<a href=\"http://londonist.com/2013/11/ticketoffices.php\"> 24 hour weekend tube</a>, so we’re talking a net loss of 750 roles. But it’s not as simple as shifting 200 people from their current jobs into Customer Service Assistant (CSA) roles though, as it’s unlikely that someone working during the day will fancy a midnight-8am Piccadilly Circus shift</p></blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f35d5ee4b0530e249db086\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T10:05:33.123Z\">10.05am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>TfL Bus Alerts is encouraging travelers and commuters still struggling to get to work to use its <a href=\"http://countdown.tfl.gov.uk/#/\">Live bus arrivals</a> tool, similar to the tickers found at many stops and on journey apps like <a href=\"http://citymapper.com/london/superrouter?\">City Mapper</a>. <br></p><p>However, be prepared for an uncomfortable journey:<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/will_sm1th/statuses/431366819417702400\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>London buses are like the Titanic 