t shy of a Kit Kat Chunky.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/parlourbird/statuses/431360363901501441\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>What a difference a day makes! Gorgeous journey in wandering along the thames... <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23london&amp;src=hash\">#london</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23walkingin&amp;src=hash\">#walkingin</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/qQC89EhPBp\">pic.twitter.com/qQC89EhPBp</a></p>&mdash; Hannah Cox (@parlourbird) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/parlourbird/statuses/431360363901501441\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f359b0e4b0530e249db081\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:47:13.894Z\">9.47am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Is the return of fleets of these classic buses the tube strike's silver lining? <br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/stickyvic_78/statuses/431359595878305792\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>It&#39;s nice to see the oldies out to give everyone a hand! Great to see them back in service! <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/INjSYQMlJm\">pic.twitter.com/INjSYQMlJm</a></p>&mdash; Vicki Haworth (@stickyvic_78) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/stickyvic_78/statuses/431359595878305792\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f35832e4b0530e249db07f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:43:06.401Z\">9.43am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Key points from the Mayor of London and RMT union leader's BBC radio interviews in the last hour.</p><p>Boris Johnson:<br></p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>Why don't they (the unions) get to the negotiating team now? Of course there's wriggle room - that's what negotiation about.</p></blockquote><p>Bob Crow in response: </p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>He wants services on Friday and Saturday night. Are you telling me you're going to run trains with people boozed off their minds and you're going to take 1,000 staff out of the system and that's safe?</p></blockquote><blockquote></blockquote> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:51:07.851Z\">at 9.51am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f356cee4b0530e249db07e\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:36:47.641Z\">9.36am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Vanessa Feltz on BBC Radio London has dedicated <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p001d7dd\">her show this morning</a> to the tube strikes. Both Boris Johnson and Bob Crow have been on air.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/VanessaOnAir/statuses/431359573501304832\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Bob Crow says more investment is needed tube staff as Underground is a growing business <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a></p>&mdash; Vanessa Feltz (@VanessaOnAir) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/VanessaOnAir/statuses/431359573501304832\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f35602e4b0530e249db07c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:31:23.094Z\">9.31am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Boris Johnson has been giving interviews outside Embankment station.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/m1nha/statuses/431355513079889920\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Bumped into good old Boris Johnson this morning <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MayorofLondon\">@MayorofLondon</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/aILIAzlk0O\">pic.twitter.com/aILIAzlk0O</a></p>&mdash; Am1nha (@m1nha) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/m1nha/statuses/431355513079889920\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f3536de4b0ab978b0f977c\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:27:35.372Z\">9.27am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Those traveling by bus are being warned to expect long queues at stops, in some places worse than yesterday, especially near underground and train stations. Overcrowding on mainline trains appears to be having a knock on effect.</p><p>The <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TfLBusAlerts\">TfL Bus Alerts</a> account reports particular problems from Stratford station on routes 25 and 108, and around Upper Street in Islington on the 43. </p><p>Here's a picture taken outside Victoria station during a tube strike in 1962. We're not sure if similarities are heartening or depressing but thanks to <a href=\"http://pirateomnibus.wordpress.com/\">The Pirate Omnibus</a> blog for the insight.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-b6b21e5d-b0f4-4522-b97d-0ce8f057c93d\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/6/1391678695241/11c3baaf-4fd6-415c-911f-d721509a5fbe-460x276.jpeg\" alt=\"1960s commuters queue outside Victoria station their own during tube strike\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>1960s commuters queue outside Victoria station their own during tube strike Photograph: The Pirate Omnibus/Wordpress</figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f351c8e4b0530e249db079\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:13:57.397Z\">9.13am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>As <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2014/feb/06/london-tube-strike-day-two-live?commentpage=1#block-52f34e12e4b0ab978b0f9778\">mentioned in more detail below</a>, there are delays on the Overground to and from Clapham Junction in part due to crowd control measures.<br></p> <figure class=\"element element-witness element-witness-image\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\" data-media-id=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0eadfe4b08e6aaede60e6/802874\"> <div class=\"element-witness--main\"> <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0eadfe4b08e6aaede60e6/802874\" itemprop=\"url\"><img src=\"https://n0tice-static.s3.amazonaws.com/image/1391674988748210d09acae3a7e8c7012407aed7e6f2f-mediumoriginalaspectdouble.jpg\" alt=\"One way access system at Clapham Junction station.\" itemprop=\"contentURL\"/></a> <figcaption> <h3 class=\"element-witness--title\" itemprop=\"name\"><a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0eadfe4b08e6aaede60e6/802874\" itemprop=\"url\">One way access system at Clapham Junction station.</a></h3> </figcaption> </div> <footer class=\"element-witness--footer\"> <p class=\"element-witness--source\">Sent via <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/\" class=\"element-witness--brand\" itemprop=\"provider\">GuardianWitness</a></p> <div class=\"element-witness--metadata\"> <p class=\"element-witness--author\" itemprop=\"author\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\"> By <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/user/WojtekStelm\" class=\"element-witness--author-name\" itemprop=\"name\">WojtekStelm</a> </p> <p class=\"element-witness--date\"> <time itemprop=\"dateCreated\" datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:23:09Z\">6 February 2014, 8:23</time> </p> </div> </footer> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:14:07.393Z\">at 9.14am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f350cee4b0530e249db077\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:10:50.019Z\">9.10am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Hammersmith and City line is operating a limited service this morning. This picture, sent into <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0eadfe4b08e6aaede60e6/802880\">GuardianWitness</a>, from Paddington station shows measures in place to limit overcrowding on the reduced number of trains.</p> <figure class=\"element element-witness element-witness-image\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\" data-media-id=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0eadfe4b08e6aaede60e6/802880\"> <div class=\"element-witness--main\"> <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0eadfe4b08e6aaede60e6/802880\" itemprop=\"url\"><img src=\"https://n0tice-static.s3.amazonaws.com/image/139167526099349d476824c770851ebb9dde30bd9b247-mediumoriginalaspectdouble.jpg\" alt=\"Traffic calming measures... \" itemprop=\"contentURL\"/></a> <figcaption> <h3 class=\"element-witness--title\" itemprop=\"name\"><a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/assignment/52f0eadfe4b08e6aaede60e6/802880\" itemprop=\"url\">Traffic calming measures... </a></h3> <div itemprop=\"description\"> <p>Paddington H&amp;C Station</p> </div> </figcaption> </div> <footer class=\"element-witness--footer\"> <p class=\"element-witness--source\">Sent via <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/\" class=\"element-witness--brand\" itemprop=\"provider\">GuardianWitness</a></p> <div class=\"element-witness--metadata\"> <p class=\"element-witness--author\" itemprop=\"author\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\"> By <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/user/MadKingSoup\" class=\"element-witness--author-name\" itemprop=\"name\">MadKingSoup</a> </p> <p class=\"element-witness--date\"> <time itemprop=\"dateCreated\" datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:27:42Z\">6 February 2014, 8:27</time> </p> </div> </footer> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T10:36:44.894Z\">at 10.36am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f35049e4b0ab978b0f977b\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:06:34.393Z\">9.06am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Station update: Vauxhall and Blackfriars underground stations are now open, the latter only until 3pm.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f34e12e4b0ab978b0f9778\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:59:22.447Z\">8.59am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The latest from the <a href=\"http://www.tfl.gov.uk/tfl/livetravelnews/realtime/tube/default.html\">TfL live updates page</a> shows minor delays on the Overground, which many commuters will have been relying on as an alternative to the underground.</p><p>There is a signal failure between West Croydon and Sydenham with no service running between these stations. Additionally, there are minor delays between Barking and Gospel Oak due to a faulty freight train.</p><p>And in a repeat of yesterday morning, overcrowding at Stratford has forced station staff to delay services between Stratford and Richmond and between Willesden Junction and Clapham Junction to ensure safety on platforms and onboard trains. </p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T09:01:19.201Z\">at 9.01am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f34ce5e4b0530e249db071\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:53:48.915Z\">8.53am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Update from the TfL Met Line: Service on the Metropolitan line has now been extended beyond Harrow-on-the-Hill out to Uxbridge thanks to a shuttle service running every 20 minutes.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/metline/statuses/431345708923633664\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Update! Shuttle service available every 20 mins from Uxbridge to Harrow on the Hill.</p>&mdash; TfL Met line (@metline) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/metline/statuses/431345708923633664\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f34c27e4b0530e249db06f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:48:36.661Z\">8.48am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Very slow moving traffic shown on TfL cameras around Stockwell and Clapham Common.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/TfLTrafficNews/statuses/431347796948840448\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>A3 is slow moving in both directions between Clapham Common and Stockwell. <a href=\"http://t.co/1peRQqoC9S\">pic.twitter.com/1peRQqoC9S</a></p>&mdash; TfL Traffic News (@TfLTrafficNews) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TfLTrafficNews/statuses/431347796948840448\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:48:50.196Z\">at 8.48am GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52f34a46e4b0ab978b0f9774\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:43:22.698Z\">8.43am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p><a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/travelnews/londoncentral\">BBC Travel</a> is reporting heavy congestion on roads into and around central London, particularly at the Blackwall Tunnel, Tottenham Hale gyratory and northbound on London Bridge.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f346d8e4b0ab978b0f976f\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:26:31.837Z\">8.26am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Central line was shut for much of yesterday morning but is currently operating in both directions. </p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f34645e4b0ab978b0f976d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:23:03.554Z\">8.23am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/tonyhenderson1/statuses/431338937416974336\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Up early to beat the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a> &amp; Waterloo is quiet Northern line straight to Totemham Court Road <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23veryearlyformeeting&amp;src=hash\">#veryearlyformeeting</a></p>&mdash; tonyhenderson (@tonyhenderson1) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/tonyhenderson1/statuses/431338937416974336\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f3453ce4b0530e249db067\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T08:21:53.647Z\">8.21am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>There seems to be a theme on Twitter of people who do persevere with the tube getting to work early thanks to it being otherwise avoided by commuters.</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/LilyScarlett91/statuses/431337735191003136\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>At work an hour early because of the <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a>. I even got a seat on the jubilee line <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23unheardof&amp;src=hash\">#unheardof</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23peaceandquiet&amp;src=hash\">#peaceandquiet</a></p>&mdash; Lily-Scarlett (@LilyScarlett91) <a href=\"https://twitter.c