-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T07:45:22.825Z\">7.45am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Roads into London are facing heavier congestion with many avoiding crowded public transport alternatives to the underground</p> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/surlysaffa/statuses/431331534206148608\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23tubestrike&amp;src=hash\">#tubestrike</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23TubeStrikeMakesMe&amp;src=hash\">#TubeStrikeMakesMe</a> furious <a href=\"http://t.co/xORj1fH9qh\">pic.twitter.com/xORj1fH9qh</a></p>&mdash; Leah illing (@surlysaffa) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/surlysaffa/statuses/431331534206148608\">February 6, 2014</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f33ccce4b0ab978b0f9760\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T07:43:42.953Z\">7.43am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Travelers began to gather before 7am, waiting for St Pancras underground station to open</p> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-902bfffc-ab28-4ac5-a75f-b68c16fe832c\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/2/6/1391672521017/5c1ca8f9-af9c-4f1c-87ae-3a7322c476d4-460x276.jpeg\" alt=\"A crowd begins to gather waiting for the underground station to open inside St Pancras station\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Inside St Pancras station Photograph: Fred McConnell/Guardian</figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52f33983e4b0ab978b0f975d\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2014-02-06T07:38:24.070Z\">7.38am <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Good morning. The London tube strike enters its second day with further station closures and delays due to disrupt this morning's commute.</p><p>The morning starts dry in the capital, however, the Met Office has issued amber warnings for heavy rain throughout the day in the South West, London and the South East. Those traveling are advised to be prepared for adverse conditions. </p><p>The London tube strike has been called in response to Transport for London’s plans to cut almost 1,000 jobs and close many ticket offices across the capital. Boris Johnson, the mayor of London, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/2014/feb/04/boris-johnson-hosts-his-lbc-phone-in-politics-live-blog#block-52f0bab9e4b0420f628a4965\">said on Tuesday</a> that the job losses could be achieved through voluntary redundancy and called ticket offices “old-fashioned technology”.</p><p>There are good services running this morning on the <b>Northern line</b>, <b>Overground</b> and <b>DLR</b>.</p><p><b>Bakerloo line </b>No service due to strike action. TfL aim to resume service at around 7am or as soon as possible after that, between Queen's Park and Elephant &amp; Castle only, with some stations closed</p><p><b>Central line</b> (closed yesterday morning) Service operating between White City and West Ruislip, Ealing Broadway and between Marble Arch and Epping and Hainault via Newbury Park</p><p><b>Circle line</b> Closed</p><p><b>District line</b> Service operating between Upminster and Ealing Broadway and High Street Kensington to Wimbleedon</p><p><b>Hammersmith and City line</b> Service operating between Hammersmith and Moorgate</p><p><b>Jubilee line</b> Operating Stanmore and Finchley Road southbound</p><p><b>Metropolitan line</b> Operating between Harrow-on-the-Hill and Aldgate</p><p><b>Piccadilly line</b> Service operating between Acton Town and Heathrow and between Arnos Grove and Cockfosters every 20 minutes</p><p><b>Victoria line </b>Service operating between Seven Sisters and Brixton</p><p><b>Waterloo and City line</b> Closed</p><p>Full details on curr